<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8" standalone="yes"?><rss version="2.0" xmlns:atom="http://www.w3.org/2005/Atom"><channel><title>Resources on Jikkou</title><link>https://www.jikkou.io/docs/providers/schema-registry/resources/</link><description>Recent content in Resources on Jikkou</description><generator>Hugo</generator><language>en</language><atom:link href="https://www.jikkou.io/docs/providers/schema-registry/resources/index.xml" rel="self" type="application/rss+xml"/><item><title>Schema Registry Subjects</title><link>https://www.jikkou.io/docs/providers/schema-registry/resources/subject/</link><pubDate>Mon, 01 Jan 0001 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate><guid>https://www.jikkou.io/docs/providers/schema-registry/resources/subject/</guid><description>&lt;div class="pageinfo pageinfo-info">
&lt;p>&lt;em>SchemaRegistrySubject&lt;/em> resources are used to define the subject schemas you want to manage on your SchemaRegistry. A
SchemaRegistrySubject resource defines the schema, the compatibility level, and the references to be associated with a
subject version.&lt;/p>

&lt;/div>

&lt;h2 id="definition-format-of-schemaregistrysubject">Definition Format of &lt;code>SchemaRegistrySubject&lt;/code>&lt;/h2>
&lt;p>Below is the overall structure of the &lt;code>SchemaRegistrySubject&lt;/code> resource.&lt;/p>
&lt;div class="highlight">&lt;pre tabindex="0" class="chroma">&lt;code class="language-yaml" data-lang="yaml">&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="nt">apiVersion&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;schemaregistry.jikkou.io/v1beta2&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The api version (required)&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">kind&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="s2">&amp;#34;SchemaRegistrySubject&amp;#34;&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The resource kind (required)&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">metadata&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">name&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;The name of the subject&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># (required)&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">labels&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>{&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>}&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">annotations&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>{&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>}&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">spec&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">schemaRegistry&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">vendor&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;vendor_name&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># (optional) The vendor of the SchemaRegistry, e.g., Confluent, Karapace, etc&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">compatibilityLevel&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;compatibility_level&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># (optional) The schema compatibility level for this subject.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">schemaType: &amp;lt;The schema format&amp;gt; # (required) Accepted values are&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">AVRO, PROTOBUF, JSON&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">schema&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">$ref&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;url or path&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">references&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># Specifies the names of referenced schemas (optional array).&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>- &lt;span class="nt">name&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;string&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The name for the reference.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">subject&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;string&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The subject under which the referenced schema is registered.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="nt">version&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">:&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="l">&amp;lt;string&amp;gt; &lt;/span>&lt;span class="w"> &lt;/span>&lt;span class="c"># The exact version of the schema under the registered subject.&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;span class="line">&lt;span class="cl">&lt;span class="w">&lt;/span>&lt;span class="p">]&lt;/span>&lt;span class="w">
&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/span>&lt;/code>&lt;/pre>&lt;/div>&lt;h3 id="metadata">Metadata&lt;/h3>
&lt;p>The &lt;code>metadata.name&lt;/code> property is mandatory and specifies the name of the &lt;em>Subject&lt;/em>.&lt;/p></description></item></channel></rss>